ABSTRACT

•

The omnibus anti-drug bill passed in the final days of the 99th Congress is a far-ranging measure containing fifteen titles and relating to almost every aspect of Federal efforts to prevent and control the abuse of drugs. In addition to making substantial changes in regulatory and enforcement statutes, the new law provides for additional appropriations of $1.7 billion for FY 1987, of which $671 million are to be used for grants to States and localities. This summary focuses on the enactment's highlights.

